132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1716
S.P. 669 In Senate, April 17, 2025
An Act to Require Family Life Education to Include a Human
Growth and Development Curriculum
Reference to the Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs suggested and ordered
printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator GUERIN of Penobscot.
Cosponsored by Representatives: GRIFFIN of Levant, JAVNER of Chester, LEMELIN of
Chelsea, TUELL of East Machias.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง1912 is enacted to read:
3 ยง1912. Human growth and development curriculum
4 1. Definition. As used in this section, unless the context otherwise indicates, "human
5 growth and development discussion" means an oral, written or digital lesson, lecture or
6 presentation about human biology related to pregnancy and human development inside the
7 uterus.
8 2. Human growth and development discussion. A school offering comprehensive
9 family life education pursuant to section 1910 shall incorporate a human growth and
10 development discussion into its curriculum. The human growth and development
11 discussion must be offered to students beginning no later than grade 3.
12 3. Videos. A human growth and development discussion must include:
13 A. A high-definition ultrasound video, at least 3 minutes in duration, showing the fetal
14 development of the brain, heart, sex organs and other vital organs in early fetal
15 development; and
16 B. A video showing the process of fertilization and every stage of fetal development
17 inside the uterus and noting significant markers in cell growth and organ development
18 of a fetus from conception to birth.
19 4. Cause of action; civil suit. The Attorney General has a cause of action to sue for
20 damages and injunctive relief and may bring a civil suit to enforce this section on behalf of
21 a resident of the State against a person that violates this section.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill requires schools offering comprehensive family life education to include a
2244 human growth and development discussion that includes an ultrasound video and a video
2255 showing the process of fertilization and every stage of fetal development inside the uterus.
2266 The Attorney General is authorized to bring a civil suit to enforce the provision.
